parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Front suspension misalignment can cause uneven tire wear, reduced traction, and loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
An uneven weight distribution at the front end of the vehicle can cause excessive wear on tires and suspension components, leading to premature failure and potentially causing loss of control.
The failure of the autobrake and parking brake can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents or collisions, especially when parking on inclines.
symptoms: The autobrake and parking brake fail to engage
the vehicle moves forward when in park position
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
